snippet.title: Kids Workout - Upper Strength
snippet.description: This Upper Body workout is great not only for making you stronger, but also helps with your posture and overall muscle balance. As kids develop it’s often just the legs that get most of the attention - running, jumping and general play usually involves moving the lower body. So it’s great to keep the upper body developing as well. Mixing up upper body, lower body and cardio workouts throughout your week will ensure you’re getting the best possible results for your whole body.

snippet.title: Kids Workout - Static Strength Workout
snippet.description:
This is a perfect workout if you’re wanting to improve your strength but aren’t feeling particularly energetic. It’s all about holding each move and contracting the muscles. 
-
Static Strength - HOLD 
Wall Sit - 45 secs
Plank - 45 secs
Push Up - hold at bottom for 10 counts x (3-5 reps)
Kneeling OPP hand and leg lift and Hold for 10 counts each side) x 3-5
- Harder version on hands and feet (Not shown on video)
Reverse plank Bent leg - Opp hand to shoulder taps x 45 secs 
- harder version straight legs

If you’re feeling brave, you can start again from the top and repeat 2-3x through. Don’t forget to LIKE and SUBSCRIBE for more workout and fitness content each Sunday morning. Subscribe to this channel here: UC5b5ycda7EBvSahVUoTytFA

snippet.title: Kids exercise workout, 20 minute fitness routine!
snippet.description:
This one is a really fun 20 minute kids workout, that includes full body exercises! And on top of that, the kids exercises were designed or chosen by a little kid (my daughter!) so you don't get any more authentic than that :D
The kids fitness routine includes exercises that work the fully body, head to toe! We have:
- frog jumps, rabbit jumps, kangaroo jumps and more for leg exercises. 
- Crab crawls, supermans, bear crawls, beetle crawls and more for core exercises.
- And then we have helicopters, bird wings and arm circles and others for arm exercises. 
- On top of that we make time to standing balance with special exercises for that too, so EVERYTHING is included!
And just like all of the videos in this series, you can train as hard as you like, either at a very high intensity and really work up a sweat (like Mr. Ten Thousand) or just get moving and have great fun (like my daughter). It's up to you! Just do your best to make it through the entire workout your own way :)

We also have lots of other fitness videos here on this channel, something for everybody to enjoy and improve their endurance, agility, improve balance, get flexibility and range of motion, get strong and much more. You're most welcome to check out what we share here, all for free :)

I do my best to reply to every comment here, so let me know if you have anything to share :) Especially if it's related to your fitness.
All the best, from,
Mr. Ten Thousand.

snippet.title: Star Wars JEDI WORKOUT
snippet.description:
'THE FORCE WILL BE WITH YOU, ALWAYS!!'...

Thats Right! In homage to the release of...‘THE RISE OF SKYWALKER', I'm Bringing to you your very own ‘STAR WARS' (Light Side) Workout. 

This workout is part of a double Star Wars release from me. This is the Light side ‘JEDI’ workout and there is also a Dark side ‘SITH’ workout.

It’s up to you to choose from the LIGHT or the DARK.

All you need is a Lightsaber, a stop-watch, and of course THE FORCE! :)

Set a timer to 30secs work and 10secs rest and perform these 5 JEDI exercises 4 times round with a 50secs rest in-between rounds.
Try to perform this 3-4 times this week and Get those JEDI Calories Burning :)

Your Exercises :-
LUKE BLASTS - 30sec
YODA BLOCKS - 30secs
QUI-GON HOLD - 30secs
FORCE FLOW - 30secs
SKYWALKER STRIKES (LEFT) - 30secs
CHEWIE CRUNCH - 30secs
SKYWALKER STRIKES (RIGHT) - 30secs

GOOD LUCK GUYS AND 'MAY THE FORCE BE WITH YOU'
